# Free-tier cloud — read before routing / troubleshooting edits

## Canonical doc

Open **`.cursor/models/ai_agent.md`**:

- **§12** — Which **rules and docs to cite** in requests (public API, ctypes, defaults, prompts).
- **§13** — **Troubleshooting** for **`api_chat` → `ai_agent.c`**: backend, lane pin, keys, order, C-built URLs, **`M4_LOG_CLOUD_LLM`**, **§13.7 outbound hostnames** (firewall allowlist).
- **§14** — **Four tiers in c-lib**: one-shot hosted completion vs **Ollama** sync/stream (**no** hosted token stream in C yet).
- **§15** — **Policy**: **`python_ai`** must not own canonical Groq/Cerebras/Gemini HTTP; **free-tier stream** roadmap in **c-lib** (approved **`api_*`**). Do **not** add new Python-only vendor paths for product chat.

## Tighter rules (do not skip)

- **New or changed `api_*` / `api.h` / FFI structs:** **`.cursor/rules/public-api-surface.mdc`** — maintainer approval.
- **Python ↔ C options:** **`.cursor/rules/python-clib-contract.mdc`**.
- **Default model strings:** **`.cursor/rules/default-models.mdc`** / **`include/ollama.h`**.

## Common mistake to avoid

**API keys do not imply hosted cloud** when **`M4_CHAT_BACKEND=ollama`**. Stream mode (`stream_cb != NULL`) currently uses Ollama only. For **egress** issues, check **§13.7** hostnames from the **same process** that loads c-lib (**§13.1**).
